WEBVTT

00:45.754 --> 00:50.050
WOMAN: There's an isolation
to the woods, isn't there?

00:50.091 --> 00:55.055
A sense of unease
in a dark wilderness.

00:55.096 --> 00:58.266
Because things disappear there.

00:58.308 --> 01:01.102
Things die there.

01:01.144 --> 01:05.065
But she wasn't afraid.
Not at first.

01:05.106 --> 01:06.483
Even though she was alone,

01:06.524 --> 01:09.819
she knew
she could survive the night.

01:09.861 --> 01:15.367
But as she got deeper into
the forest, she smelled it.

01:15.408 --> 01:19.996
The rot. The smell of death.

01:20.038 --> 01:23.416
CONTINUES ON RADIO: She finally
found them in the clearing.

01:23.458 --> 01:25.418
By now, the long, hot summer

01:25.460 --> 01:28.213
had caused the bodies
to putrefy.

01:28.254 --> 01:30.632
The flies and maggots
were crawl...

01:30.674 --> 01:31.925
No fucking way.

01:31.966 --> 01:34.135
(CRASHING)

01:40.975 --> 01:42.769
(EXHALES)

01:53.988 --> 01:55.907
(PHONE BEEPS)

02:26.730 --> 02:28.815
(BREATHING RAPIDLY)

02:28.857 --> 02:30.650
-(GASPS)
-(TWIG SNAPS)

02:31.943 --> 02:33.862
(RUSTLING)

02:40.869 --> 02:42.203
(GASPS)

02:44.330 --> 02:46.249
(RUSTLING)

02:59.054 --> 03:00.972
(GASPS)

03:02.891 --> 03:04.726
(RUSTLING)

03:12.734 --> 03:14.319
(EXHALES)

03:17.947 --> 03:21.826
(SCREECHING SOUND)

03:35.757 --> 03:39.928
(GASPS) Oh!

03:41.513 --> 03:44.933
-(ENGINE STALLS)
-(GROANS)

03:44.974 --> 03:46.685
-(AXE THUDS)
-(SCREAMS)

03:46.726 --> 03:50.605
-(SCREAMING CONTINUES)
-(REPEATED AXE BLOWS)

05:34.000 --> 05:36.711
I can't make you straight.

05:39.506 --> 05:42.133
I don't wanna make you straight.

05:42.175 --> 05:46.054
Gay people are A-OK with me.

05:47.555 --> 05:52.686
If you're happy the way you are,
then more power to you.

05:54.813 --> 05:56.439
And I know what you're thinking.

05:56.481 --> 05:58.108
You hear the words
"gay conversion camp,"

05:58.149 --> 06:00.985
and you start to imagine all
kinds of homophobic bullshit.

06:01.027 --> 06:05.198
Well, that is not
what we're about here.

06:05.240 --> 06:07.033
And let me tell you
another thing.

06:07.075 --> 06:12.122
God...
God doesn't hate you either.

06:12.163 --> 06:14.666
And any son of a bitch
that tells you otherwise

06:14.708 --> 06:15.750
is a bigoted asshole.

06:15.792 --> 06:18.420
And that is officially
the last time

06:18.461 --> 06:20.922
that you're gonna hear
about the man upstairs.

06:20.964 --> 06:22.882
I promise you.

06:24.050 --> 06:28.722
But I'm guessing
that some of you are here

06:28.763 --> 06:32.017
because in some way
you're not happy.

06:32.058 --> 06:34.102
Maybe you don't fit in.

06:34.144 --> 06:35.770
People make fun of you.

06:35.812 --> 06:38.815
Maybe you wanna find
some new kind of peace,

06:38.857 --> 06:41.151
a new way of thinking
about yourself.

06:41.192 --> 06:47.282
Well, you give us this week,
and we might be able to help.

06:47.323 --> 06:50.243
And if not, just enjoy
the sunshine,

06:50.285 --> 06:52.912
and work on your tan.

06:52.954 --> 06:57.000
OK. Let me introduce you
to my colleagues.

06:57.042 --> 07:00.170
They do all the real work.
I just cash the checks.

07:00.211 --> 07:04.174
This is Dr. Cora Whistler.
She is our licensed therapist,

07:04.215 --> 07:07.719
and as you might have guessed
from the name, my wife.

07:07.761 --> 07:09.512
She who must be obeyed.

07:09.554 --> 07:10.930
Next to her is Nurse Molly

07:10.972 --> 07:13.099
who takes care of any
little mishaps that may occur.

07:13.141 --> 07:16.770
Molly's new here,
so take it easy on her.

07:16.811 --> 07:19.439
And that's Zane,
our athletics director

07:19.481 --> 07:21.149
and a former student here.

07:21.191 --> 07:22.901
So, he knows all the ropes.

07:22.942 --> 07:26.112
And, boys, he's taken,
so hands off.

07:27.822 --> 07:30.283
And that beautiful woman
right there

07:30.325 --> 07:31.910
is Sarah, Zane's fiancé.

07:31.951 --> 07:34.454
She's our activities director,

07:34.496 --> 07:37.123
and she is going
to keep you busy.

07:37.165 --> 07:38.583
Believe you me.

07:38.625 --> 07:40.335
(WHEELBARROW CREAKS)

07:40.377 --> 07:42.128
And over here we have Balthazar.

07:42.170 --> 07:44.506
That's our handyman,
all-around Mr. Fix it.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.841
Say hello, Balthazar!

07:49.678 --> 07:54.808
And that, finally, is old Duke.

07:54.849 --> 08:01.648
Duke is one old hound dog.
So please treat him kindly.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.527
OK. I'm gonna need you
to hand over

08:05.568 --> 08:08.071
all your cell phones
and computers.

08:08.113 --> 08:09.447
(ALL GASP)

08:09.489 --> 08:13.159
As well as any medicines,
narcotics, or cigarettes

08:13.201 --> 08:14.244
that you may have.

08:14.285 --> 08:16.079
Cell phones don't work
out here anyway,

08:16.121 --> 08:18.039
and I'm glad to say
that we don't have any Wi-Fi.

08:18.081 --> 08:22.669
So we are off the grid which
will be a nice change, I'm sure.

08:22.711 --> 08:25.547
Molly, if you would. Thank you.

08:27.716 --> 08:30.760
OK. Let me tell you
how the next week is gonna work.

08:30.802 --> 08:34.514
We have a number of planned
activities and therapy sessions

08:34.556 --> 08:36.641
that we would like you
to be part of.

08:36.683 --> 08:39.561
But other than that,
you're on your own.

08:39.602 --> 08:42.772
We do have
one hard-and-fast rule here.

08:42.814 --> 08:44.733
And it's about respect.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.359
We deal
with some sensitive issues,

08:46.401 --> 08:50.488
and we expect you to treat
your fellow students with care.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.574
And allow them their dignity.

08:54.242 --> 08:56.202
This is a safe space.

08:56.244 --> 08:57.746
For everyone.

08:58.872 --> 09:01.666
And this is
the most important thing

09:01.708 --> 09:03.918
that I want to say to you.

09:05.879 --> 09:08.590
I know that many of you are here

09:08.631 --> 09:11.968
only because your parents
made you.

09:12.010 --> 09:15.889
And while their intentions
may be honorable,

09:15.930 --> 09:18.933
only you can know
what's best for you.

09:18.975 --> 09:20.602
Because the idea of this place

09:20.643 --> 09:24.564
is not to come out
more straight or less gay.

09:24.606 --> 09:26.858
Of course we hope
that through your time here

09:26.900 --> 09:29.027
you will discover
a gender normative lifestyle

09:29.069 --> 09:31.279
that is authentic for you but...

09:32.447 --> 09:36.618
you must find your own truth.

09:37.827 --> 09:39.954
Let us help you do that.

09:40.622 --> 09:42.040
Please.

09:45.752 --> 09:49.673
OK. So, uh, why don't you
head to your cabins?

09:49.714 --> 09:51.257
Settle in. Unpack.

09:51.299 --> 09:54.969
We'll meet in the lodge in say,
uh, a half hour and get started.

09:55.011 --> 09:58.139
Boys' cabin over there.
Girls' cabin over there.

10:15.490 --> 10:17.409
Yes.

10:17.450 --> 10:22.288
-So this is a thing.
-OK.

10:22.330 --> 10:26.793
I'm trans and nonbinary.
I use they/them pronouns.

10:26.835 --> 10:31.006
As in, they can't believe
they're at this fucking camp.

10:32.757 --> 10:34.676
I'm assuming you don't have
an all-gender cabin.

10:34.718 --> 10:38.263
No. Not currently.
Obviously we need one.

10:39.055 --> 10:40.682
Maybe so.

10:42.851 --> 10:47.105
This place
is all about inclusion.

10:48.773 --> 10:50.567
About being with other kids

10:50.608 --> 10:52.861
and finding
a sense of community.

10:52.902 --> 10:57.032
So it's important
that nobody be isolated.

10:57.073 --> 11:01.703
I acknowledge
and respect your transition.

11:01.745 --> 11:04.289
So head over to the boys' cabin,

11:04.330 --> 11:07.500
and if you don't feel
comfortable there,

11:07.542 --> 11:10.045
we can talk about other options.

11:10.879 --> 11:12.380
How's that?

11:14.257 --> 11:15.592
Sounds great.

11:15.633 --> 11:18.845
Great. Thanks.

11:18.887 --> 11:22.307
And thanks for understanding.

11:37.822 --> 11:41.034
-(SCOFFS) They?
-Yes, ma'am.

11:41.076 --> 11:42.994
(LAUGHS)

11:49.751 --> 11:54.422
I want to start with a simple
question. Why are you here?

12:00.428 --> 12:02.138
Toby?

12:04.599 --> 12:06.893
I'm here because

12:06.935 --> 12:11.773
I don't want to be
a big flaming fruit anymore.

12:11.815 --> 12:16.569
I wanna play hockey
and drink non-light beer

12:16.611 --> 12:18.863
like all the normal guys.

12:20.615 --> 12:23.451
I made a deal with my parents.
If I spent the week here,

12:23.493 --> 12:25.704
I could go to New York
and see Moulin Rouge!.

12:25.745 --> 12:26.746
(ALL CHUCKLE)

12:26.788 --> 12:28.331
You look more like
a Sondheim man.

12:28.373 --> 12:30.083
-Queen!
-Well, you're looking at a guy

12:30.125 --> 12:32.711
that saw the original production
of Merrilytwice.

12:32.752 --> 12:35.839
-Bitch!
-(LAUGHS)

12:35.880 --> 12:39.384
Veronica. What about you?
Why are you here?

12:39.426 --> 12:40.969
Um...

12:42.554 --> 12:44.097
-No.
-MAN: Please.

12:44.139 --> 12:46.891
There's no judgments in
this room, OK? Why are you here?

12:46.933 --> 12:50.437
Cause I'm bisexual.
So, I'm a freak and I hate it.

12:50.478 --> 12:53.982
All right? Are you happy?

12:57.277 --> 12:59.112
I'm a swimmer.

12:59.154 --> 13:03.575
I know I can get a scholarship,
but not like this.

13:04.409 --> 13:07.245
Not like I am.

13:07.287 --> 13:09.289
I mean, in the locker room
I don't know where to look.

13:09.330 --> 13:11.624
I get so tense
I have to, like, throw up.

13:11.666 --> 13:14.002
No one knows in school.

13:15.170 --> 13:17.505
I'd die if they found out.

13:20.175 --> 13:25.722
It's like I'm pretending
to be this thing and...

13:25.764 --> 13:27.932
I don't wanna pretend anymore.

13:27.974 --> 13:29.934
My parents made me come.

13:29.976 --> 13:31.353
I just wanna fit in.

13:31.394 --> 13:33.438
It was come here or you're out
on the street, honey.

13:33.480 --> 13:36.066
When I go to college, I'm gonna
pledge my dad's fraternity,

13:36.107 --> 13:39.110
which I kind of have to,
or he's gonna, like, disown me.

13:39.152 --> 13:40.653
I mean, house seats.

13:40.695 --> 13:42.864
I'm not that complicated,
honestly.

13:42.906 --> 13:45.075
I just wanna be
like everybody else.

13:45.116 --> 13:46.201
Fifth row, center.

13:46.242 --> 13:49.037
I wanna give my parents
grandkids.

13:50.997 --> 13:52.123
Like my sister did.

13:52.165 --> 13:54.000
I'm only here to shut
my parents up

13:54.042 --> 13:55.585
and get some fucking peace.

13:55.627 --> 14:00.882
I have zero interest in not
being gay. I love me some lady.

14:00.924 --> 14:04.135
I hear it all the time. "Fag."

14:04.177 --> 14:07.889
"There goes the fag."
"Blow me, fag."

14:10.058 --> 14:11.351
And the laughter.

14:11.393 --> 14:13.520
I don't wanna waste my soul
fighting this thing.

14:13.561 --> 14:15.188
I just wanna make it go away.

14:15.230 --> 14:17.941
Sometimes I wish
I was invisible.

14:17.982 --> 14:19.609
I wanna be entertained.

14:19.651 --> 14:22.028
I wanna live my life.

14:22.070 --> 14:24.364
I wanna fit in.

14:24.406 --> 14:26.241
I wanna be loved.

14:44.134 --> 14:45.927
Jordan, you're awfully quiet.

14:46.970 --> 14:51.433
Uh, I don't have
anything to add.

14:52.225 --> 14:53.893
Is he gonna get away with that?

14:53.935 --> 14:55.520
-They.
-Whatever the fuck.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.355
We all talked.

14:57.397 --> 15:00.400
Jordan, this is
a circle of trust.

15:00.442 --> 15:03.695
We all shared.
Why are you here?

15:09.117 --> 15:11.953
I come from a religious family.

15:12.871 --> 15:15.623
They don't understand me.

15:15.665 --> 15:19.627
We made a deal.
If I come here for a week...

15:20.879 --> 15:23.465
they'll let me legally
emancipate myself.

15:25.383 --> 15:28.011
Emancipate yourself to do what?

15:29.929 --> 15:31.681
Be myself.

15:37.020 --> 15:39.939
All right. I wanna thank you all

15:39.981 --> 15:43.401
for your trust
and for your honesty.

15:43.443 --> 15:47.322
I've been through therapy, so I
know how difficult this can be.

15:49.324 --> 15:53.453
Being at peace with yourself,
with your true self,

15:53.495 --> 15:56.164
that's the hardest thing to do,
isn't it?

15:57.624 --> 16:01.044
OK. That's it for today.

16:01.086 --> 16:02.962
So, dinner is in an hour,

16:03.004 --> 16:06.132
and we'll start up again
in the morning.

16:06.174 --> 16:08.009
Enjoy the night.

16:29.280 --> 16:30.782
Wrong team, fuckwad.

17:39.059 --> 17:40.435
(GROANS)

17:40.477 --> 17:43.563
(BIRDS SING)

17:46.983 --> 17:49.778
(CLOCK TICKS)

18:37.242 --> 18:40.412
(FOOTSTEPS)

19:03.184 --> 19:05.186
(GASPS)

19:18.408 --> 19:20.702
Gentlemen,
you have a new roommate.

19:20.744 --> 19:23.163
All I ask from you people
is honesty.

19:23.204 --> 19:25.457
Honesty
in how you treat each other.

19:25.498 --> 19:27.625
And honesty in
how you present yourselves.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.502
Lying is not going
to get us anywhere.

19:29.544 --> 19:31.504
I wasn't lying.
This is who I am.

19:31.546 --> 19:33.465
Jordan treated me with respect

19:33.506 --> 19:36.092
by being truthful
about their transition.

19:36.134 --> 19:39.262
You did not. Simple as that.

19:39.304 --> 19:41.389
OK, everyone out front.
Ten minutes for roll call.

19:41.431 --> 19:45.560
