(BLOWS WHISTLE)

21:07.809 --> 21:09.352
-Go!
-Pull!

21:09.394 --> 21:11.604
Pull it. Pull it. Come on.

21:17.444 --> 21:19.571
(SONG PLAYS OVER DIALOGUE)

22:51.329 --> 22:53.081
WOMAN: Can I help you?

22:56.292 --> 22:59.546
I need my pills.
The ones you took.

22:59.587 --> 23:03.842
-I'm sorry, I can't.
-No, honey, I need them.

23:05.051 --> 23:06.803
Sit down. Please.

23:14.102 --> 23:16.980
I don't make the rules here.
If you wanna talk to Owen...

23:17.022 --> 23:18.773
I need them.

23:24.446 --> 23:27.615
It's the, uh, the Zoloft.

23:31.119 --> 23:33.163
This is a pretty powerful
antidepressant.

23:33.204 --> 23:35.707
I don't think I can give it
to you without checking with...

23:35.749 --> 23:37.917
Without checking
with one of those fuckers

23:37.959 --> 23:39.336
who runs the place?

23:39.377 --> 23:40.962
Come on.

23:42.881 --> 23:46.134
As misguided as they may be
about some things,

23:46.176 --> 23:47.635
I can't just ignore protocol.

23:47.677 --> 23:50.138
It's not Zoloft, all right?

23:56.519 --> 23:59.647
-Estradiol.
-It's an estrogen hormone.

24:02.442 --> 24:04.361
-I made a deal with my parents.
-I know.

24:04.402 --> 24:06.363
You come here,
or they throw you out.

24:06.404 --> 24:09.074
ALEXANDRA:
It's... It's not that.

24:09.115 --> 24:10.658
At all.

24:17.540 --> 24:19.709
When I turned 18,

24:19.751 --> 24:23.004
I thought there was nothing
they could do to stop me.

24:24.005 --> 24:25.882
But I was wrong.

24:27.467 --> 24:31.888
I have a younger brother,
and he means the world to me.

24:31.930 --> 24:34.224
And I mean the world to him.

24:34.265 --> 24:36.976
And they said that if I did not
come to this place,

24:37.018 --> 24:40.522
that they would never let me
see him again.

24:44.734 --> 24:48.238
Anyway, I need my pills.

24:55.620 --> 24:57.539
Our secret.

25:09.634 --> 25:14.139
This camp, do you even believe
in any of this?

25:15.515 --> 25:18.143
I believe in healing.
That's all.

25:19.060 --> 25:21.646
Maybe you should believe
in dignity.

25:27.318 --> 25:28.903
(DOOR CLOSES)

25:54.429 --> 25:55.889
(LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS) ??

25:57.599 --> 26:00.602
Up and at 'em, gents!

26:02.103 --> 26:03.772
Get dressed!

26:04.856 --> 26:06.900
It's time to play.

26:33.468 --> 26:34.928
OK, let's hold up here.

26:34.969 --> 26:40.183
Everyone, please remove your
blindfolds and gather round.

26:40.225 --> 26:42.227
Come on. Step up.

26:43.395 --> 26:46.064
Let me tell you something
that I've learned.

26:46.106 --> 26:48.942
Self-reliance is a cornerstone

26:48.983 --> 26:52.195
of self-confidence
and self-love.

26:52.237 --> 26:56.199
But trust in your community
is vital.

26:56.241 --> 26:57.742
You're not alone.

26:57.784 --> 27:02.997
There is always help if you
are brave enough to ask for it.

27:04.666 --> 27:08.336
Look at your partners.
Go on. Look.

27:10.213 --> 27:13.675
Trust them. Accept them.

27:14.342 --> 27:16.219
Love them.

27:16.261 --> 27:20.223
OK. Each pair head off
in a different direction,

27:20.265 --> 27:24.561
walk around for ten minutes
and stop.

27:24.602 --> 27:27.355
And we will see you
in the morning.

27:27.689 --> 27:29.315
What?

27:31.526 --> 27:33.695
Do you have a problem with that?

27:35.989 --> 27:37.532
No, sir.

27:37.574 --> 27:39.826
I'm sure the Geneva Convention
has some protocol about this.

27:39.868 --> 27:43.038
Well, the next time I'm in
Switzerland, I'll ask them.

27:44.539 --> 27:46.374
Now, start walking.

27:47.751 --> 27:50.337
Go on. Move.

27:50.628 --> 27:52.797
Go!

27:56.718 --> 28:00.055
-This should be cozy.
-Fuck me.

28:26.539 --> 28:29.084
(SIGHS)

28:29.125 --> 28:32.045
(SIGHS) I don't know
that I'm ready for all this.

28:32.087 --> 28:35.882
Yeah, you don't really give off
camper vibes.

28:35.924 --> 28:39.928
No. I mean...

28:39.969 --> 28:45.308
Well, Alexander...
Alexandra, whatever,

28:45.350 --> 28:48.311
I don't really know
any trans people.

28:48.353 --> 28:49.688
He really surprised me.

28:49.729 --> 28:55.360
-It's "she", actually.
-I can't even get that right.

28:55.402 --> 28:58.571
I just don't think
like you guys do.

28:58.613 --> 29:00.573
I live
in this super-straight suburb.

29:00.615 --> 29:02.075
Everyone's the same.

29:04.703 --> 29:06.788
Except me.

29:09.624 --> 29:14.379
-I know what you mean.
-Do you?

29:14.421 --> 29:20.176
(LAUGHS) Look at you.
You're so chill.

29:20.218 --> 29:25.140
Try that haircut in my school.
No one would talk to you.

29:26.182 --> 29:30.979
-I'd talk to me.
